[1
Date: Wed, 22 Mar 2000 17:11:06 -0700
From: Lynwood. A Fiedler <Lynwood.A.Fiedler@usda.gov>

A summary article describing the role vampire bats play in transmitting
rabies to cattle in Latin America and the method developed to reduce these
losses is: Mitchell, G.C. 1986. Vampire bat control in Latin America.
Pages 151-164 in National Research Council. Ecological Knowledge and
Environmental Problem-Solving: Concepts and Case Studies. National Academy
Press. The technique of capturing live vampire bats near cattle, smearing
their backs with an anticoagulant paste and releasing them to return to
their roost for mutual grooming was very cost-beneficial.
--
Lynwood Fiedler (retired)
USDA/National Wildlife Research Center
Fort Collins, CO, USA
e-mail: Lynwood.A.Fiedler@usda.gov
